Here is someone who is just repairing my kitchen floor. And I'm pretending to still have a job and working from home while writing for Too Hot to Handle.
If I could just damn open the file. (Damn OneDrive.)
*Hacker voice* I'm in.
And then he starts drilling really loudly. Great.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to blast my air purifier to full capacity, but I can smell the wood dust, so even if he's not a mask opponent, it would be totally okay. Do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't before he's gone.
At least I finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yes, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing a search and replace for … ➡️ Ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I'll stick with that. Natural language is usually choppy, especially when one is emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he's almost done.
He went outside to cut something (it sounds that way anyway). I secretly checked how far he had gotten. There's still a lot left to do :(
Still 7 pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's pretty neat – mainly changes to the writing and very small corrections to direct speech and I need to make everything a bit more compact. But I really could use a break and some tea, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he's started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
Er hat mir erzählt, dass er einen Kostenvoranschlag für den gesamten Boden gemacht hätte, aber die Vermieter waren zu knauserig und haben nur für den Teil neben der Tür bezahlt, der nicht mehr in Ordnung ist. Fühlt sich gleich viel besser an.
Das Haus wird durchgelüftet und in der Küche läuft mein Luftreiniger, während ich im Garten einen Tee trinke!
